				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">doppleganger is correct.<br /><br />The original quote is just a more verbose way of saying WRAM A &lt;&gt; WRAM B does not work, regardless of DMA transfer direction. Think about it from a hardware perspective: how can the same chip with one address+data bus be read from and written to at the same time at different locations?<br /><br />So use an A-bus address ($43x2-4) that is not WRAM (nor a mirror of it.) ROM is the surefire method, but you could also do SRAM if you have some.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

